      <h2 class="title">RAJGIR GLASS BRIDGE</h2>
      <p class="desc">
        The Rajgir Glass Bridge is a thrilling tourist attraction located in the scenic hills of Rajgir, Bihar. 
        Inspired by the famous Zhangjiajie Glass Bridge in China, it offers breathtaking views of the lush greenery and the valleys below.
      </p>
      <p class="desc">
        Suspended at a height of around **200 feet**, the bridge is made of **see-through toughened glass**, allowing visitors to walk "in the air". 
        It has quickly become one of the most visited adventure spots in Bihar.
      </p>
      <p class="desc">
        Located inside the **Nature Safari Park**, the Glass Bridge is part of a larger eco-tourism initiative that also includes **zip-lining, archery, wall climbing, and more**. 
        The site is especially popular among youth and families looking for an exciting escape into nature.
      </p>

